comments.message:
This is the kind of logic I'd really like contained in each sensor instance.  Ideally hwmontempsensor, or maybe Sensor would have something like

"onPowerStateChange"  for which we can do all this logic, and ideally do


if (power == "power state I care about"){
   if (!i2cDevice){
      i2cDevice.emplace(....);
   }
} else{
  i2cDevice.reset()
}

That keeps us RAII safe in all cases.

Kinda nitpicky, but I would've preferred something like

std::shared_ptr<I2cDevice> i2cDev;
if (findI2CDev != newSensors.end()){
   i2cDev = findI2cDev->second;
}

Just a little bit clearer, and avoids the ternary and having to explicitly declare nullptr.
